1
00:00:00,968 --> 00:00:03,971
♪

2
00:00:09,109 --> 00:00:11,111
( Singing in Japanese )

3
00:00:44,711 --> 00:00:46,680
♪

4
00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:48,715
( Fire crackling )

5
00:01:00,460 --> 00:01:03,129
Jotaro: So this is Saudi Arabia,

6
00:01:03,163 --> 00:01:05,766
about 8,800 kilometers
from Japan.

7
00:01:08,402 --> 00:01:11,772
And it’s been around four weeks
since we began our journey.

8
00:01:13,340 --> 00:01:15,042
If we don’t hurry,

9
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:16,743
we’ll be in serious trouble.

10
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:28,088
Kakyoin.

11
00:01:31,825 --> 00:01:35,762
Polnareff: Hey, jotaro. What do
you think is up with kakyoin?

12
00:01:35,796 --> 00:01:37,798
First he nearly
kills us in his sleep.

13
00:01:37,831 --> 00:01:40,801
Now he looks like he’s
coming apart at the seams.

14
00:01:40,834 --> 00:01:43,337
He even went after the baby.

15
00:01:43,370 --> 00:01:45,072
Something’s just not right.

16
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:48,108
If you ask me,
he’s at his wit’s end.

17
00:01:53,814 --> 00:01:56,250
( Baby hisses )

18
00:01:56,283 --> 00:01:58,418
( Chuckles )

19
00:01:58,452 --> 00:02:02,056
For a second there, I thought
he’d actually figured me out,

20
00:02:02,089 --> 00:02:05,659
but now the poor louse
is half-doubting himself.

21
00:02:05,692 --> 00:02:09,262
To top things off, we’re
in the middle of the desert.

22
00:02:09,296 --> 00:02:12,633
All I have to do is wait
until they fall asleep.

23
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:15,235
If there’s no one
to wake them up...

24
00:02:15,269 --> 00:02:16,670
( Laughs )

25
00:02:17,738 --> 00:02:20,074
Polnareff:
Something smells good.

26
00:02:20,107 --> 00:02:21,542
What kind of food is that?

27
00:02:21,575 --> 00:02:23,243
Joseph: This is baby food.

28
00:02:23,277 --> 00:02:26,180
It’s a delicious concoction
of milk, egg yolks,

29
00:02:26,213 --> 00:02:28,649
bananas, and bread
all stewed together.

30
00:02:28,682 --> 00:02:30,350
So you wanna taste it?

31
00:02:30,384 --> 00:02:31,585
( Polnareff gulps )

32
00:02:33,220 --> 00:02:34,254
Joseph: Hmm?

33
00:02:35,355 --> 00:02:36,556
Polnareff: Wow!

34
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:39,293
This is flat-out amazing!
Give me more!

35
00:02:39,326 --> 00:02:40,761
Joseph: Easy now.

36
00:02:40,794 --> 00:02:43,697
At this rate, there won’t
be any left for the baby.

37
00:02:43,730 --> 00:02:47,300
Baby: You incompetent bastard,
how dare you eat my food?

38
00:02:47,334 --> 00:02:48,836
I’m wasting away over here,

39
00:02:48,869 --> 00:02:51,572
so hurry up,
and feed me, damn it.

40
00:02:51,605 --> 00:02:53,807
( Groans )

41
00:02:53,841 --> 00:02:54,809
( Yelps )

42
00:02:54,842 --> 00:02:57,645
It’s--it’s a scorpion.

43
00:02:57,678 --> 00:03:00,614
♪

44
00:03:00,647 --> 00:03:02,682
What am I going to do?

45
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:08,722
( Gasps )

46
00:03:12,893 --> 00:03:14,361
( Sighs )

47
00:03:14,394 --> 00:03:15,862
That was a close one.

48
00:03:15,896 --> 00:03:18,265
( Gasps )

49
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:21,235
( Kakyoin shuddering )

50
00:03:21,268 --> 00:03:24,171
Baby: Crap baskets.
Kakyoin was watching.

51
00:03:25,506 --> 00:03:27,775
Kakyoin: He killed the scorpion.

52
00:03:27,808 --> 00:03:29,677
So I was right.

53
00:03:29,710 --> 00:03:31,545
That baby really is a...

54
00:03:31,578 --> 00:03:34,214
Baby: Shit. What now?

55
00:03:34,248 --> 00:03:36,217
Joseph: You’re not
getting any more.

56
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:38,786
Kakyoin: Mr. Joestar,
polnareff, did you see that?

57
00:03:38,819 --> 00:03:39,787
Both: Huh?

58
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:41,555
Kakyoin: I was right after all.

59
00:03:41,588 --> 00:03:42,823
That baby’s not normal.

60
00:03:42,856 --> 00:03:45,225
He just killed a scorpion.

61
00:03:45,259 --> 00:03:46,494
He stabbed it.

62
00:03:46,527 --> 00:03:49,530
The boy skewered it
with his own safety pin.

63
00:03:50,664 --> 00:03:52,933
- Joseph: Eh?
- Polnareff: Eh?

64
00:03:52,966 --> 00:03:55,335
Joseph: Kakyoin, hold on a sec.

65
00:03:55,369 --> 00:03:57,404
What the hell
are you talking about?

66
00:03:57,437 --> 00:03:59,773
The baby, damn it.
That kid isn’t human.

67
00:03:59,806 --> 00:04:03,576
He’s not even a year old yet,
but he knew what a scorpion was,

68
00:04:03,610 --> 00:04:06,813
and he killed it
with those tiny hands of his.

69
00:04:06,847 --> 00:04:08,515
Joseph: A scorpion?

70
00:04:08,549 --> 00:04:09,817
Where is it?

71
00:04:09,850 --> 00:04:11,819
- Kakyoin: It’s in here.
- Joseph: Huh?

72
00:04:11,852 --> 00:04:13,253
Kakyoin: Where’d it go?

73
00:04:13,287 --> 00:04:15,422
There should be
an impaled scorpion here.

74
00:04:15,455 --> 00:04:16,823
Joseph: Hmm.

75
00:04:18,458 --> 00:04:20,627
Kakyoin: It’s gone.

76
00:04:22,496 --> 00:04:23,931
( Joseph scoffs )

77
00:04:23,964 --> 00:04:25,332
Kakyoin: I swear it’s true.

78
00:04:25,365 --> 00:04:26,733
He must have
hidden it somewhere!

79
00:04:26,767 --> 00:04:29,203
Check his clothes!

80
00:04:29,236 --> 00:04:30,804
Joseph: We get the point.

81
00:04:30,838 --> 00:04:32,807
Knock it off, kakyoin.
That’s enough.

82
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:34,508
Kakyoin: Mr. Joestar.

83
00:04:34,541 --> 00:04:37,210
Joseph: Like I said before,
you’re clearly exhausted.

84
00:04:37,244 --> 00:04:38,979
- Kakyoin: But--
- Joseph: Let’s table this,

85
00:04:39,012 --> 00:04:40,514
at least for tonight.

86
00:04:40,547 --> 00:04:42,516
We’ll talk
after you’ve calmed down.

87
00:04:42,549 --> 00:04:43,784
( Kakyoin gasps )

88
00:04:44,785 --> 00:04:45,986
( Polnareff groans )

89
00:04:49,823 --> 00:04:52,559
♪

90
00:04:52,593 --> 00:04:55,329
( Joseph blowing )

91
00:04:55,362 --> 00:04:57,764
Okay, here’s the choo-choo.

92
00:04:57,798 --> 00:04:59,733
It’s dewicious.

93
00:05:02,369 --> 00:05:05,939
Uh-oh. What’s the matter?

94
00:05:05,973 --> 00:05:07,908
You were hungry
a minute ago, right?

95
00:05:07,941 --> 00:05:10,010
Did you lose that big appetite?

96
00:05:10,043 --> 00:05:11,578
Ahh...

97
00:05:11,612 --> 00:05:14,748
Baby: Would you stop
shoving that spoon in my face?

98
00:05:14,781 --> 00:05:16,916
I can’t eat right now,
you idiot!

99
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:18,251
Joseph: Huh?

100
00:05:18,285 --> 00:05:19,453
Kakyoin: Mr. Joestar, listen!

101
00:05:19,486 --> 00:05:21,321
I’m not imagining things.

102
00:05:21,355 --> 00:05:24,258
I don’t know where he could have
hidden the blasted scorpion,

103
00:05:24,291 --> 00:05:26,326
but i’m sure
that he’s a stand user,

104
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,862
and I have just the thing

105
00:05:27,895 --> 00:05:30,498
to prove to you
that i’m telling the truth.

106
00:05:30,531 --> 00:05:31,932
Do you see these cuts?

107
00:05:31,965 --> 00:05:33,900
Read what the letters spell out.

108
00:05:33,934 --> 00:05:35,869
Can’t you see
that it’s a warning?

109
00:05:35,903 --> 00:05:38,706
It must have happened to me
when I was sleeping earlier.

110
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:42,309
Joseph: Oh, my god!

111
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:43,944
( Baby gasps )

112
00:05:43,977 --> 00:05:47,681
Jotaro: Kakyoin, you didn’t
do that to yourself, did you?

113
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:49,015
Kakyoin: Say what?

114
00:05:49,049 --> 00:05:53,520
Polnareff: I-it’s finally
happened. Kakyoin.

115
00:05:53,554 --> 00:05:56,424
Joseph: Oh, my god.

116
00:05:56,456 --> 00:05:58,625
♪

117
00:05:58,659 --> 00:06:01,795
Baby: You colossal buffoon.
How stupid can you be?

118
00:06:01,829 --> 00:06:03,831
Didn’t you realize
if you showed them

119
00:06:03,864 --> 00:06:06,867
the cuts on your arm,
they’d think you were crazy?

120
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:10,637
Kakyoin: What’s going on?
Did I make things even worse?

121
00:06:10,671 --> 00:06:14,341
Then it looks like
I have no other choice.

122
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:17,477
I’ll have to rely on force.

123
00:06:17,511 --> 00:06:19,813
Hierophant green!

124
00:06:19,847 --> 00:06:20,848
( Baby wails )

125
00:06:23,617 --> 00:06:26,653
( Kakyoin groans )

126
00:06:26,687 --> 00:06:28,322
Polnareff: It’s no use.

127
00:06:28,355 --> 00:06:31,558
Damn it. The guy has
completely lost his mind.

128
00:06:31,592 --> 00:06:33,961
Kakyoin: This can’t
be happening.

129
00:06:33,994 --> 00:06:38,565
I’m certain of what I saw,
jotaro.

130
00:06:38,599 --> 00:06:42,470
His stand was the one we fought
in our dreams, polnareff.

131
00:06:43,637 --> 00:06:46,573
We can’t fall asleep,
Mr. Joestar.

132
00:06:47,608 --> 00:06:49,376
Believe me, everyone,

133
00:06:49,409 --> 00:06:52,746
if we fall asleep,
we’ll all be killed.

134
00:06:52,779 --> 00:06:54,514
Please, you guys...

135
00:06:54,548 --> 00:06:56,984
You have to believe me.

136
00:06:59,386 --> 00:07:01,922
Baby: Yes!
My secret is still safe,

137
00:07:01,955 --> 00:07:04,357
which means the end is near.

138
00:07:04,391 --> 00:07:07,361
Your petty mistrust
just cost you your lives.

139
00:07:07,394 --> 00:07:09,696
Victory is mine, fools.

140
00:07:09,730 --> 00:07:10,998
Polnareff: I can’t believe it.

141
00:07:11,031 --> 00:07:13,500
If he’s like this,
does that mean kakyoin

142
00:07:13,534 --> 00:07:15,569
can’t fight or travel
with us anymore?

143
00:07:15,602 --> 00:07:16,937
( Joseph sighs )

144
00:07:16,970 --> 00:07:18,939
We’ll discuss it in the morning.

145
00:07:18,972 --> 00:07:21,608
Let’s get some sleep.

146
00:07:21,642 --> 00:07:24,478
Polnareff,
give me a hand moving kakyoin.

147
00:07:24,511 --> 00:07:25,746
Polnareff: Sure thing.

148
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:28,015
Joseph: Jotaro,
you bring the sleeping bags.

149
00:07:28,048 --> 00:07:29,016
Jotaro: Right.

150
00:07:29,049 --> 00:07:30,751
( Baby gags )

151
00:07:31,952 --> 00:07:33,387
Joseph: You say something?

152
00:07:33,420 --> 00:07:35,122
Polnareff: No.
He’s just really heavy.

153
00:07:35,155 --> 00:07:37,724
Baby: I’ve got you
right where I want you.

154
00:07:37,758 --> 00:07:39,126
I’m gonna slice you up

155
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:41,628
and scatter your remains
all over the desert.

156
00:07:41,662 --> 00:07:42,830
( Spits )

157
00:07:42,863 --> 00:07:45,432
♪

158
00:07:48,569 --> 00:07:50,838
( Polnareff snoring )

159
00:08:05,152 --> 00:08:06,754
Joseph: Hmm?

160
00:08:07,955 --> 00:08:09,623
What in the world?

161
00:08:09,656 --> 00:08:11,758
Why are we in the middle
of an amusement park?

162
00:08:11,792 --> 00:08:13,594
We were just out in the desert.

163
00:08:13,627 --> 00:08:15,095
- Polnareff: That’s right.
- Joseph: Eh?

164
00:08:15,128 --> 00:08:17,631
I know this place.

165
00:08:17,664 --> 00:08:20,500
Jotaro, Mr. Joestar,
be on your guard.

166
00:08:20,534 --> 00:08:22,936
M-my memory is coming back.

167
00:08:22,970 --> 00:08:26,574
We’ve been transported
to a dream world...

168
00:08:26,607 --> 00:08:28,509
A horrible one.

169
00:08:28,542 --> 00:08:29,877
This is bad.

170
00:08:29,910 --> 00:08:31,945
We’ve entered
a world of nightmares.

171
00:08:31,979 --> 00:08:34,081
Joseph:
Oh, so it’s a dream, huh?

172
00:08:34,114 --> 00:08:37,084
You had me a little worried
for a minute there.

173
00:08:37,117 --> 00:08:39,519
Polnareff: Don’t make
the same mistake that I did!

174
00:08:39,553 --> 00:08:43,090
Listen, everything kakyoin
said to us earlier is true.

175
00:08:43,123 --> 00:08:45,459
Baby...stand.

176
00:08:45,492 --> 00:08:47,728
We are in enemy territory.

177
00:08:47,761 --> 00:08:50,831
I know this may be hard
for you to believe,

178
00:08:50,864 --> 00:08:53,100
but the stand user is that baby.

179
00:08:57,070 --> 00:09:00,574
There’s no one left to wake you
from your slumber now,

180
00:09:00,607 --> 00:09:02,909
and that means
there’s absolutely no way

181
00:09:02,943 --> 00:09:05,612
for you to escape
death 13’s world.

182
00:09:07,281 --> 00:09:11,085
I’ll finally finish you off
once and for all.

183
00:09:11,118 --> 00:09:13,520
♪

184
00:09:13,554 --> 00:09:17,058
Polnareff: Why did I have to hit
kakyoin and knock him out?

185
00:09:17,090 --> 00:09:19,092
But since I did that...

186
00:09:19,126 --> 00:09:22,096
He should already be here!
We’ve got to find him.

187
00:09:22,129 --> 00:09:24,565
Where in the world
are you, kakyoin?!

188
00:09:24,598 --> 00:09:27,101
I have to find a way
to make this up to you.

189
00:09:27,134 --> 00:09:28,702
Joseph: P-polnareff!

190
00:09:28,735 --> 00:09:31,037
Good lord, what is
going on with your hair?!

191
00:09:31,071 --> 00:09:33,140
Did you mess up brushing it?!

192
00:09:33,173 --> 00:09:34,207
Polnareff: Huh?

193
00:09:36,743 --> 00:09:37,744
( Yells )

194
00:09:37,778 --> 00:09:40,547
( Screaming )

195
00:09:45,285 --> 00:09:46,553
Joseph: Polnareff!

196
00:09:48,822 --> 00:09:50,090
Jotaro: What the...

197
00:09:51,124 --> 00:09:53,259
Joseph: Ahh! What’s going on?

198
00:09:53,293 --> 00:09:55,796
My prosthetic hand is...

199
00:09:55,829 --> 00:09:56,797
Yah!

200
00:09:56,830 --> 00:09:58,699
Holy shit bricks!

201
00:09:58,732 --> 00:10:01,001
( Groans )

202
00:10:01,034 --> 00:10:02,802
( Laughter )

203
00:10:04,104 --> 00:10:06,573
Polnareff: How are we
supposed to fight this?

204
00:10:06,607 --> 00:10:07,808
It’s maddening.

205
00:10:07,841 --> 00:10:10,644
Damn, anything can happen
in this world.

206
00:10:10,677 --> 00:10:13,180
There are no rules here.
Nothing makes sense.

207
00:10:13,213 --> 00:10:16,817
As long as we’re in this place,
we’re completely at his mercy.

208
00:10:16,850 --> 00:10:20,320
Wait. I remember
there being one rule...

209
00:10:21,321 --> 00:10:22,589
His murder weapon.

210
00:10:22,623 --> 00:10:24,191
If he wants
to slice us to pieces,

211
00:10:24,224 --> 00:10:28,795
then he’ll have to use
his stand...

212
00:10:29,863 --> 00:10:32,966
And nothing but his stand.

213
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,736
Death 13: Lali-ho!

214
00:10:37,271 --> 00:10:39,039
( All gasping )

215
00:10:44,077 --> 00:10:46,980
Death 13: Lali-ho!

216
00:10:47,014 --> 00:10:49,049
Jotaro: Ora! Star...

217
00:10:49,082 --> 00:10:50,984
Polnareff: Jotaro, it’s no use!

218
00:10:51,018 --> 00:10:53,687
It’s impossible for us to bring
our stands into this world!

219
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:55,188
Jotaro: Platinum!

220
00:10:56,823 --> 00:10:58,325
( Polnareff gasps )
That’s weird.

221
00:10:58,358 --> 00:10:59,993
His stand manifested.

222
00:11:01,295 --> 00:11:02,897
( Star platinum grunts )

223
00:11:02,930 --> 00:11:05,299
( Yelling )

224
00:11:05,332 --> 00:11:06,300
Ora!

225
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:07,801
( Jotaro groans )

226
00:11:07,835 --> 00:11:09,904
( Star platinum laughs )

227
00:11:11,138 --> 00:11:12,139
Ora?

228
00:11:14,241 --> 00:11:15,442
Ora?

229
00:11:16,910 --> 00:11:18,145
Ora.

230
00:11:18,178 --> 00:11:19,646
( Babbles )

231
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:21,115
( Grunts ) Ora?

232
00:11:21,148 --> 00:11:24,318
Ora. ( Laughs )

233
00:11:24,351 --> 00:11:26,353
Death 13: Lali-ho.

234
00:11:26,386 --> 00:11:28,121
Surprise. I’m a fake.

235
00:11:29,456 --> 00:11:31,792
Oh, the overwhelming power,

236
00:11:31,825 --> 00:11:35,362
the absolute terror,
it’s so much fun!

237
00:11:35,395 --> 00:11:38,765
A stand is
a manifestation of the mind,

238
00:11:38,799 --> 00:11:41,969
and what are dreams
if not the mind laid bare?

239
00:11:42,002 --> 00:11:45,439
My death 13 has trapped you
within your subconscious,

240
00:11:45,472 --> 00:11:49,676
which is why you can’t summon
your precious stands.

241
00:11:49,710 --> 00:11:50,844
Although...

242
00:11:52,045 --> 00:11:53,446
Things might be different

243
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:57,684
had you summoned your stands
before you fell asleep.

244
00:11:57,718 --> 00:11:59,086
( Head rattles )

245
00:11:59,119 --> 00:12:01,688
Then, they would have
appeared here with you,

246
00:12:01,722 --> 00:12:03,357
just like your clothes,
sleeping bags,

247
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:05,192
and your prosthetic hand.

248
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:10,797
Death 13 will never be forced
to face another stand in battle.

249
00:12:10,831 --> 00:12:13,801
And, as you know, the only thing
that can defeat a stand

250
00:12:13,834 --> 00:12:17,204
is another stand,
so i’ll always come out on top.

251
00:12:17,237 --> 00:12:19,339
( Laughs )

252
00:12:19,373 --> 00:12:22,243
Now that I have all of you
in my cross hairs,

253
00:12:22,276 --> 00:12:24,278
how about you give me a scream,

254
00:12:24,311 --> 00:12:27,214
one that captures the joy
and elation i’m about to feel

255
00:12:27,247 --> 00:12:29,015
at my easy victory?!

256
00:12:29,049 --> 00:12:30,017
( Men gasp )

257
00:12:30,050 --> 00:12:31,518
Death 13: Lali--ho?

258
00:12:33,053 --> 00:12:35,756
Oh, it’s just one
of the fakes I made.

259
00:12:36,823 --> 00:12:38,391
♪

260
00:12:38,425 --> 00:12:40,394
( Gags )

261
00:12:40,427 --> 00:12:42,429
What? I don’t understand.

262
00:12:42,462 --> 00:12:44,998
This one doesn’t seem
to be a fake.

263
00:12:46,066 --> 00:12:47,935
This is the real hierophant.

264
00:12:47,968 --> 00:12:49,403
( Coughs )

265
00:12:51,872 --> 00:12:53,407
Joseph: It’s normal.

266
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,809
Polnareff: Look! It’s kakyoin.

267
00:12:55,843 --> 00:12:58,112
Kakyoin’s right there.

268
00:12:58,145 --> 00:13:00,114
Kakyoin: Obviously
it slipped your notice

269
00:13:00,147 --> 00:13:01,915
that i’d already summoned
my hierophant

270
00:13:01,949 --> 00:13:03,884
by the time
I was knocked unconscious.

271
00:13:03,917 --> 00:13:06,319
What’s more,
I had it burrow underground

272
00:13:06,353 --> 00:13:09,923
to conceal itself from detection
just before I fell asleep.

273
00:13:09,957 --> 00:13:11,058
( Death 13 groans )

274
00:13:11,091 --> 00:13:13,093
You can’t do this.

275
00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:16,997
Kakyoin: Now, it’s time
for your punishment, baby.

276
00:13:17,030 --> 00:13:19,499
( Manishu gagging )

277
00:13:19,533 --> 00:13:21,301
Damn that bastard.

278
00:13:21,335 --> 00:13:23,571
( Death 13 yelling )

279
00:13:24,805 --> 00:13:27,174
Let go!

280
00:13:27,207 --> 00:13:28,775
Kakyoin: Give up, death 13.

281
00:13:28,809 --> 00:13:32,146
I had hierophant place himself
in your blind spot.

282
00:13:32,179 --> 00:13:34,848
If you keep up
this futile struggling...

283
00:13:36,884 --> 00:13:39,086
Regardless of the fact
you’re a baby,

284
00:13:39,119 --> 00:13:41,154
it’ll snap your neck
like a twig.

285
00:13:41,188 --> 00:13:42,956
Joseph: Kakyoin!

286
00:13:42,990 --> 00:13:45,359
- ( Kakyoin grunts )
- Joseph: Kakyoin,

287
00:13:45,392 --> 00:13:48,128
the three of us
owe you an enormous apology.

288
00:13:48,161 --> 00:13:49,529
Polnareff: I thought
after the hell

289
00:13:49,563 --> 00:13:51,165
you’d been through on this trip,

290
00:13:51,198 --> 00:13:52,900
you might have suddenly
lost your sanity.

291
00:13:52,933 --> 00:13:55,002
I mean, a baby stand user?

292
00:13:55,035 --> 00:13:57,304
You were fighting
this battle alone,

293
00:13:57,337 --> 00:14:00,407
and for that, i’m sorry.

294
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,975
Kakyoin: Don’t worry, polnareff.

295
00:14:02,009 --> 00:14:03,210
It couldn’t have been helped.

296
00:14:03,243 --> 00:14:05,145
You were the reason
I found a way

297
00:14:05,179 --> 00:14:07,415
to bring my stand
to the dream world with me.

298
00:14:07,447 --> 00:14:09,549
If you hadn’t hit me,
we’d be stuck here

299
00:14:09,583 --> 00:14:11,452
without a way
to defend ourselves,

300
00:14:11,485 --> 00:14:14,021
so, in a way,
this is all thanks to you.

301
00:14:14,054 --> 00:14:16,023
Polnareff: Yeah?
Do you mean that?

302
00:14:16,056 --> 00:14:18,458
Gee, now I feel conflicted
about the whole thing.

303
00:14:18,492 --> 00:14:20,060
That’s embarrassing.

304
00:14:20,093 --> 00:14:21,561
( Giggling )

305
00:14:21,595 --> 00:14:23,597
( Manishu gagging )

306
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:26,533
Kakyoin hasn’t killed me yet,
because i’m a baby.

307
00:14:26,567 --> 00:14:28,069
( Laughs )

308
00:14:28,101 --> 00:14:32,205
Kakyoin, your compassion
will cost you your life.

309
00:14:32,239 --> 00:14:33,907
In case you’ve forgotten,

310
00:14:33,941 --> 00:14:37,111
you’re all still trapped
inside my nightmare world.

311
00:14:37,144 --> 00:14:40,314
♪

312
00:14:40,347 --> 00:14:42,883
( Kakyoin gasps )

313
00:14:44,518 --> 00:14:46,887
Polnareff: Uh-oh.
What’s up with these clouds?

314
00:14:46,920 --> 00:14:48,188
Joseph: No kidding.

315
00:14:48,222 --> 00:14:50,191
They’re changing shape
and closing in.

316
00:14:51,925 --> 00:14:55,395
Kakyoin: You’d better not
try anything funny, death 13.

317
00:14:57,931 --> 00:15:00,066
Jotaro: Kakyoin,
you have to get hierophant

318
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:02,436
away from his back
before it’s too late.

319
00:15:03,604 --> 00:15:04,905
Kakyoin: How did--

320
00:15:06,273 --> 00:15:08,041
death 13: I’ll chop you in half!

321
00:15:11,144 --> 00:15:12,512
Kakyoin: Impossible.

322
00:15:14,181 --> 00:15:16,016
How could he do that?

323
00:15:16,049 --> 00:15:19,553
He--he chopped himself in half.

324
00:15:21,989 --> 00:15:24,558
All: Kakyoin! No!

325
00:15:24,591 --> 00:15:26,960
Death 13: Lali-ho.

326
00:15:26,994 --> 00:15:28,896
Haven’t you figured it out yet?

327
00:15:28,929 --> 00:15:32,399
Death 13’s body is as hollow
as the space between your ears.

328
00:15:33,634 --> 00:15:35,536
Manishu: My stand
is only comprised

329
00:15:35,569 --> 00:15:38,939
of the head, arms,
and the giant scythe it wields.

330
00:15:38,972 --> 00:15:41,208
You gigantic ignoramuses.

331
00:15:42,309 --> 00:15:43,377
Let’s see.

332
00:15:43,410 --> 00:15:45,279
Given the way the stands work,

333
00:15:45,312 --> 00:15:47,514
kakyoin’s body
should also be split in two

334
00:15:47,548 --> 00:15:49,216
inside the sleeping bag.

335
00:15:49,249 --> 00:15:51,184
Kakyoin: Nah, just kidding.

336
00:15:51,218 --> 00:15:52,453
All: Kakyoin!

337
00:15:52,486 --> 00:15:54,321
Joseph: Hey,
you sure you’re all right?

338
00:15:54,354 --> 00:15:56,623
Kakyoin: Hah.
Please take a closer look.

339
00:15:56,657 --> 00:15:59,193
Surely you know hierophant
isn’t that careless.

340
00:15:59,226 --> 00:16:01,128
He wouldn’t just stay
on the enemy’s back

341
00:16:01,161 --> 00:16:02,629
without a plan in the wings.

342
00:16:02,663 --> 00:16:04,632
( Death 13 gasps )

343
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:08,202
( Shuddering )

344
00:16:10,204 --> 00:16:11,939
Manishu:
He’s not chopped in half.

345
00:16:11,972 --> 00:16:14,074
He’s turned into
a snakelike thing,

346
00:16:14,107 --> 00:16:16,576
and he’s slithering into my ear!

347
00:16:16,610 --> 00:16:18,378
♪

348
00:16:18,412 --> 00:16:21,282
( Death 13 yelling )

349
00:16:29,056 --> 00:16:31,125
My arm is moving on its own!

350
00:16:31,158 --> 00:16:33,160
( Yelling )

351
00:16:33,193 --> 00:16:34,995
No! It’s coming in!

352
00:16:35,028 --> 00:16:37,364
( Yelling )

353
00:16:40,467 --> 00:16:43,337
Kakyoin: I told you before,
my stand was in your blind spot,

354
00:16:43,370 --> 00:16:45,739
and your scythe
couldn’t cut him.

355
00:16:45,772 --> 00:16:47,574
Now, then, unless you’d
like to be destroyed

356
00:16:47,608 --> 00:16:49,276
from the inside out,

357
00:16:49,309 --> 00:16:52,746
how about you do me a favor
and heal the cuts on my arm?

358
00:16:52,779 --> 00:16:55,015
Anything is possible
in a dream, right?

359
00:16:55,048 --> 00:16:57,584
So healing a cut should be easy.

360
00:16:57,618 --> 00:16:59,386
Death 13: R-right.

361
00:17:03,557 --> 00:17:05,692
( Sizzling )

362
00:17:09,730 --> 00:17:12,633
Kakyoin: All right, everyone,
time to wake up.

363
00:17:12,666 --> 00:17:14,301
- ( All grumbling )
- ( Clangs pan )

364
00:17:14,334 --> 00:17:15,735
( Polnareff groans )

365
00:17:15,769 --> 00:17:18,238
Kakyoin: Come on, polnareff.
Up and at ’em.

366
00:17:18,272 --> 00:17:20,508
There’s a nice breakfast
waiting for you.

367
00:17:24,611 --> 00:17:27,280
Polnareff: I feel like I had
a terrible dream last night.

368
00:17:27,314 --> 00:17:29,082
Joseph: You and me both.

369
00:17:29,116 --> 00:17:32,119
I can’t remember it, but I
have the sneaking suspicion

370
00:17:32,152 --> 00:17:33,687
that it was terrifying.

371
00:17:34,688 --> 00:17:36,356
( Polnareff gasps ) Kakyoin.

372
00:17:37,424 --> 00:17:38,392
Are you okay?

373
00:17:38,425 --> 00:17:39,526
How are you feeling?

374
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:40,628
Kakyoin: I’m fine.

375
00:17:40,661 --> 00:17:42,429
Polnareff: What?
Are you positive?

376
00:17:42,462 --> 00:17:45,265
’cause you were acting like
a deranged lunatic last night.

377
00:17:45,299 --> 00:17:46,667
You even carved letters
in your...

378
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:47,768
Arm.

379
00:17:49,102 --> 00:17:50,270
Wait. What?

380
00:17:50,304 --> 00:17:52,740
Where did the wound go?

381
00:17:52,773 --> 00:17:56,477
Kakyoin: All right, I think i’ll
change the baby’s diaper now.

382
00:17:57,511 --> 00:17:59,580
Polnareff: What in the world?

383
00:17:59,613 --> 00:18:02,449
Kakyoin:
It’s morning, sleepyhead.

384
00:18:02,482 --> 00:18:03,616
Polnareff: He seems to be

385
00:18:03,650 --> 00:18:05,318
getting along famously
with the baby.

386
00:18:05,352 --> 00:18:07,454
Maybe I just dreamed
the whole thing.

387
00:18:07,487 --> 00:18:08,655
( Kakyoin laughs )

388
00:18:08,689 --> 00:18:10,591
Well, then,
did you have a good rest?

389
00:18:10,624 --> 00:18:13,127
Polnareff: Oh, well. Never mind.

390
00:18:14,795 --> 00:18:16,263
Kakyoin: Mm-hmm.

391
00:18:16,296 --> 00:18:17,731
( Manishu gasping )

392
00:18:19,766 --> 00:18:21,601
Kakyoin: Everyone’s forgotten.

393
00:18:21,635 --> 00:18:26,073
A stand whose very existence
is completely forgotten,

394
00:18:26,106 --> 00:18:28,442
what a strange creature.

395
00:18:28,475 --> 00:18:31,078
But I haven’t
forgotten anything.

396
00:18:31,111 --> 00:18:33,547
Since I brought my stand
into the dream with me,

397
00:18:33,580 --> 00:18:35,282
my memories are intact.

398
00:18:36,483 --> 00:18:38,685
Listen,
because you’re just a baby,

399
00:18:38,719 --> 00:18:40,421
I won’t eliminate you.

400
00:18:40,454 --> 00:18:42,456
I won’t even injure you.

401
00:18:42,489 --> 00:18:44,725
We’ll take you to a nearby town.

402
00:18:44,758 --> 00:18:47,427
You need to be returned
to your mother.

403
00:18:47,461 --> 00:18:50,698
However, don’t come
anywhere near us again.

404
00:18:50,731 --> 00:18:53,467
If you do,
you’ll have to be punished...

405
00:18:56,136 --> 00:18:58,872
In a manner such as this.

406
00:18:58,906 --> 00:19:01,409
Manishu: Huh? Is that my poop?

407
00:19:02,643 --> 00:19:04,645
( Gasping )

408
00:19:07,714 --> 00:19:09,749
Joseph: Oh, kakyoin.

409
00:19:09,783 --> 00:19:12,452
I see you’ve made some
baby food for the little lad.

410
00:19:12,486 --> 00:19:14,188
Kakyoin: Yes.

411
00:19:14,221 --> 00:19:17,458
Joseph: Good work. I’m sure
he must be starving by now.

412
00:19:18,625 --> 00:19:21,862
Manishu: Hey, no, you wouldn’t.

413
00:19:21,895 --> 00:19:23,897
♪

414
00:19:23,931 --> 00:19:27,201
Joseph: Eat up.
These yum-yums are dewicious.

415
00:19:27,234 --> 00:19:29,570
Say, "ahh."

416
00:19:30,871 --> 00:19:33,173
Ahh.

417
00:19:33,207 --> 00:19:35,443
This again? What’s the problem?

418
00:19:35,475 --> 00:19:37,777
It’s as if he
doesn’t like the stuff.

419
00:19:37,811 --> 00:19:40,480
At this rate,
i’ll have to force-feed him.

420
00:19:40,514 --> 00:19:42,783
Manishu: Stop!

421
00:19:42,816 --> 00:19:44,785
Polnareff: You can’t force it,
Mr. Joestar.

422
00:19:44,818 --> 00:19:47,754
If you do, he’ll just end up
hating it even more.

423
00:19:47,788 --> 00:19:50,224
In special cases like this...

424
00:19:50,257 --> 00:19:51,692
( Manishu grunting )

425
00:19:51,725 --> 00:19:53,393
Polnareff: Ah, coochie-coo.

426
00:19:53,427 --> 00:19:55,829
Ah, coochie-coochie-
coochie-coochie-coo.

427
00:19:55,863 --> 00:19:58,165
Ah, coochie-coochie-
coochie-coo.

428
00:19:58,198 --> 00:19:59,633
( Manishu wails )

429
00:19:59,666 --> 00:20:01,635
( Swallows )

430
00:20:02,769 --> 00:20:03,903
( Crying )

431
00:20:03,937 --> 00:20:06,807
Joseph: I told you
it was delicious.

432
00:20:06,840 --> 00:20:08,542
Kakyoin: Ba-dum-bum.

433
00:20:15,782 --> 00:20:16,816
♪

434
00:20:16,850 --> 00:20:18,185
Narrator: Joestar and the others

435
00:20:18,218 --> 00:20:19,653
have now crossed
the arabian peninsula

436
00:20:19,686 --> 00:20:21,721
and are currently making
their way across the red sea

437
00:20:21,755 --> 00:20:25,359
as they prepare to enter Egypt,
but...

438
00:20:26,793 --> 00:20:29,763
Jotaro: Hey, old man,
something’s off.

439
00:20:29,796 --> 00:20:31,865
You’re going
the wrong direction.

440
00:20:31,899 --> 00:20:33,901
If you’re headed to Egypt,

441
00:20:33,934 --> 00:20:36,336
shouldn’t you be traveling
directly west?

442
00:20:36,370 --> 00:20:37,705
Both: Hmm?

443
00:20:37,738 --> 00:20:41,242
Jotaro: You seem to be heading
toward that island.

444
00:20:41,275 --> 00:20:43,511
Joseph: That’s right.
Nice deduction.

445
00:20:43,544 --> 00:20:45,646
I’ve had my reasons
for keeping this to myself,

446
00:20:45,679 --> 00:20:49,716
but before we arrive in Egypt,
we need to make a slight detour.

447
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:51,752
Someone is waiting for us
on the island.

448
00:20:51,785 --> 00:20:53,520
- Kakyoin: Huh?
- Polnareff: Hmm.

449
00:20:53,554 --> 00:20:54,755
Joseph: He’s a man

450
00:20:54,788 --> 00:20:57,758
who is extremely important
to our journey.

451
00:20:57,791 --> 00:21:00,360
Polnareff: What is that
supposed to mean?

452
00:21:06,033 --> 00:21:08,035
♪

453
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:22,349
♪ All the old paintings
on the tomb ♪

454
00:21:22,382 --> 00:21:24,618
♪ they do the sand dance,
don’t you know ♪

455
00:21:24,651 --> 00:21:25,752
♪ if they move too quick

456
00:21:25,786 --> 00:21:27,321
♪ oh, whey, oh

457
00:21:27,354 --> 00:21:29,289
♪ they’re falling down
like a domino ♪

458
00:21:29,323 --> 00:21:31,625
♪ all the bazaar men
by the nile ♪

459
00:21:31,658 --> 00:21:33,727
♪ they got the money on a bet

460
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:34,928
♪ gold crocodiles

461
00:21:34,962 --> 00:21:36,464
♪ oh, whey, oh

462
00:21:36,496 --> 00:21:38,531
♪ they snap their teeth
on your cigarette ♪

463
00:21:38,565 --> 00:21:40,667
♪ foreign types
with the hookah pipes say ♪

464
00:21:40,701 --> 00:21:42,937
♪ whey, oh, whey, oh

465
00:21:42,970 --> 00:21:46,674
♪ ay, whey, oh, whey, oh

466
00:21:47,774 --> 00:21:50,410
♪ walk like an Egyptian

467
00:22:01,655 --> 00:22:04,358
♪ The blond waitresses
take their trays ♪

468
00:22:04,391 --> 00:22:06,460
♪ they spin around,
and they cross the floor ♪

469
00:22:06,493 --> 00:22:07,728
♪ they’ve got the moves

470
00:22:07,761 --> 00:22:08,729
♪ oh, whey, oh

471
00:22:08,762 --> 00:22:09,763
♪ you drop your drink

472
00:22:09,796 --> 00:22:11,064
♪ then they bring you more

473
00:22:11,098 --> 00:22:13,534
♪ all the school kids
so sick of books ♪

474
00:22:13,567 --> 00:22:15,736
♪ they like the punk
and the metal band ♪

475
00:22:15,769 --> 00:22:16,970
♪ when the buzzer rings

476
00:22:17,004 --> 00:22:18,472
♪ oh, whey, oh

477
00:22:18,505 --> 00:22:20,474
♪ they’re walking
like an Egyptian ♪

478
00:22:20,507 --> 00:22:22,609
♪ all the kids
in the marketplace say ♪

479
00:22:22,643 --> 00:22:24,845
♪ whey, oh, whey, oh

480
00:22:24,878 --> 00:22:29,649
♪ ay, whey, oh, whey, oh

481
00:22:29,683 --> 00:22:32,753
♪ walk like an Egyptian

